                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful, by well-trained hand</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, vivid vermilion.</seg>The name of the scribe (and
                        probably the place of his origin) has been erased from the concluding
                        supplication formula on <locus target="#57rb">57rb</locus>.<date>First half
                           of 20th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipit of Text I; initial lines (one
                           or two first lines) of prayers; names of Ethiopian prelates; directives
                           for the ministers; some separated letters of nomina sacra (fols. 38ra);
                           elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.
                           
 On the incipit page of Text I (fol. 5r), a few lines are rubricated
                           (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1va">ff. 1va-4</locus>
                           <desc>rb: Excerpt from the Anaphora of the Apostles (Benediction of St
                              Basil?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in a careful secondary hand. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#57vb">f. 57vb-58</locus>
                           <desc>rb: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> Partly in Amharic, crudely written in pencil in a
                           secondary hand and hardly readable. The note mentions that the book was
                           donated by rās<note> Gabra Mädhǝn to the church Qarsabar Mikāʾel in Ṭǝrr
                              13 (?) [19]39 A.M. (= January 1946 A.D.) during the time of Ḫāyla
                              Śǝllāse I (r. 1930-74) and Bishop Marqos (r. 1937-1951, as Bishop of
                              Tǝgray and Eritrea). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Crude note in pen: <locus target="#4v">4v</locus>.
                           - Crude notes written in the margins: <locus target="#10v">10v</locus>,
                           17v. 
 - Pen trials: <locus target="#58v">58v</locus>.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings are indicated by the names of the
                              days of the week crudely written in the upper margin in a recent
                              secondary hand, in pen: ዘሰሉስ (?): <locus target="#10v">fol.
                                 10v</locus> ዘረብዕ: <locus target="#17v">fol. 17v</locus> ዘሐሙስ:
                                 <locus target="#25r">fol. 25r</locus> ዘአርብ: <locus target="#35r">fol. 35r</locus> ዘቀዳም: <locus target="#40v">fol. 40v</locus> ዘእሁድ:
                                 <locus target="#47v">fol. 47v</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="partly">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two wooden boards covered with tooled reddish-brown
                           leather; textile inlays.
 Two pairs of sewing stations.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="leather"/>
                           <material key="textile"/>
                        </decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Endbands"/>
